# Owner: csf-utils (cc-skills-utils plugin)
# Pin: qmd==0.1.1 (do NOT auto-upgrade; reinstall loses this patch)
# Why: upstream qmd-py v0.1.1 defaults to `paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2`
#   which is a weaker model than the locally-available `all-mpnet-base-v2`
#   (768-dim, best English semantic similarity, materially stronger retrieval
#   quality on this operator's wiki corpus). The wiki DB has been rebuilt with
#   the new model; reverting to the upstream default would silently make every
#   embedding mismatched with the stored vectors.
# Pre-existing state note: same as qmd_cli_main.patch - this patch assumes the
#   surrounding code is in the English-translated state. A fresh upstream
#   install is Chinese; the one-line change applies cleanly either way (it's
#   a single default-value swap with no surrounding text dependence).
# Re-apply after any `pip install --upgrade qmd` / Python reinstall:
#   cd <site-packages>/qmd/llm && git apply <this file>
#   (or hand-swap the default value on the `model_name` parameter)
# Verify:
#   python -c "from qmd.llm.sentence_tf import SentenceTransformerBackend; import inspect; src = inspect.getsource(SentenceTransformerBackend.__init__); assert 'all-mpnet-base-v2' in src, 'patch missing'"
# DB rebuild (required if reverting from a different model):
#   qmd embed --collection wiki --force
# Source: /design run 10d616f8 (2026-07-20). See
#   P:/.data/wiki/concepts/qmd-patch-durability-strategy.md
# =============================================================================

